threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a DDoS botnet agent, likely a variant of Gafgyt (Bashlite) or a related IoT malware family. It exhibits several malicious behaviors: it daemonizes upon execution, contains a hardcoded C2 IP address (5.59.248.136), and includes multiple specialized DDoS attack modules. Specifically, sub_406b50 and sub_407300 implement Layer 7 HTTP floods using randomized cookies and a large database of legitimate User-Agents to evade detection. Function sub_4059c0 implements SSDP (Simple Service Discovery Protocol) scanning for network discovery or amplification. The binary also features a process killer (sub_406090) designed to terminate competing malware by iterating through PIDs and calling SIGKILL, and a remote shell execution module using /bin/sh.
